data.enText: connected with or located on the outside of sth/sb
the external walls of the building
The lotion is for external use only (= only for the skin and must not be swallowed) .
happening or coming from outside a place, an organization, your particular situation, etc.

data.chText: 内外因结合导致了公司的倒闭。
data.enText: A combination of internal and external factors caused the company to close down.

data.chText: 外部因素对经济的压力
许多外在因素都可能影响人的心情。
data.enText: Many external influences can affect your state of mind.

data.chText: 来自（学校或机构）以外的；外来的
data.enText: coming from or arranged by sb from outside a school, a university or an organization

data.chText: 校外主考人 / 评定人
外部审计员将核实这些账目。
data.enText: An external auditor will verify the accounts.

data.chText: 政府决心减少本国的外债。
data.enText: The government is committed to reducing the country's external debt.
the Minister of State for External Affairs

data.chText: 这栋建筑内外均已修复。
data.enText: The building has been restored externally and internally.

data.chText: 这所大学有许多外界资助的研究项目。
data.enText: The university has many externally funded research projects.

simple_means.memory_skill: extern 外来的 + al …的→ 外面的，表面的

means: 来自(学校或机构)以外的

ex.enText: He saw her to the outer door.
I heard a voice in the outer room.

synonyms.bx: 只作定语，指距离中心、内部较远的，或相对而言在外的。

ex.enText: the external appearance of the church

ex.chText: 皮肤的外层相对来说不透水。
ex.enText: The external layer of the skin is relatively impermeable to water.

synonyms.bx: 指某事物或人体外部的。

ex.chText: 她表现出很有信心的样子以掩盖内心的紧张。
ex.enText: An outward show of confidence concealed her nervousness.

ex.chText: 这些房子从外观上看是相同的。
ex.enText: These houses look the same in outward view.

synonyms.bx: 只作定语，指人或事物的外表的，但有时并非真实。

example: he enjoyed the solemn externals of religion

tr: happening or arising or located outside or beyond some limits or especially surface

example: an external concern for reputation"- A.R.Gurney,Jr
extraneous light in the camera spoiled the photograph

value.def: External is used to indicate that something is on the outside of a surface or body, or that it exists, happens, or comes from outside.

example.ex: ...a much reduced heat loss through external walls.
example.tran: 大幅降低的外墙热损失

example.ex: Vitamins can be applied externally to the skin.
example.tran: 维生素可以外用于皮肤。

value.def: External means involving or intended for foreign countries.

example.tran: 该共和国与外国的边界

example.ex: ...protecting the value of the mark both internally and externally.
example.tran: 维持马克在国内外的币值

value.def: External means happening or existing in the world in general and affecting you in some way.

example.ex: Such events occur only when the external conditions are favorable.
example.tran: 这种事情只有在外部条件有利时才会发生。

value.def: External experts, for example external examiners, come into an organization from outside in order to do a particular job fairly and impartially, or to check that a particular job was done properly.

example.ex: There must be externally moderated tests.
example.tran: 一定要有外聘人员负责审核评分的考试。

value.def: If medicine is for external use, it is intended to be used only on the outside of your body, and not to be eaten or drunk.
